  <note type="source">Smith's Dictionary: "Blaesus, an ancient Italian poet, born at Capreae, who
    wrote serio-comic plays (σπουδογέλοιοι) in Greek. (Steph. Byz. s. v. Καπριη.) Two of these
    plays, the Μεσοτρίβας and Σατοῦρνος, are quoted by Athenaeus (iii. p. 111c., xi. p. 487c.), and
    Hesychius refers to Blaesus...."</note>
